tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Renal function is impaired as indicated by elevated creatinine. All other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, and lipids, are within or near normal limits, except for mildly low AST and HDL cholesterol. No acute metabolic derangements are evident. Recommend clinical correlation for renal insufficiency and monitoring of cardiovascular risk factors.
